llowing best describes the primary congenital anomaly associated with folate deficiency during early pregnancy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Spina bifida","Cleft palate","Cardiac septal defects","Renal agenesis","Limb reduction defects"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESpina bifida\u003C/strong\u003E is strongly associated with folate deficiency during early pregnancy. This neural tube defect occurs when the neural tube fails to close properly during embryonic development, typically between days 21-28 post-conception.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile the other options represent important congenital anomalies, they are not primarily linked to folate deficiency:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECleft palate\u003C/strong\u003E is more commonly associated with genetic and environmental factors\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECardiac septal defects\u003C/strong\u003E have multiple causes including genetic factors\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERenal agenesis\u003C/strong\u003E is typically related to genetic and developmental pathway disruptions\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELimb reduction defects\u003C/strong\u003E are more commonly associated with vascular disruption or teratogens\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis is why folate supplementation (0.4 daily) is recommended for all women planning pregnancy or in early pregnancy, ideally starting at least one month before conception. Higher doses (5mg daily) are recommended for women at increased risk of folate deficiency (diabeties, obesity, anticonvulsant therapy, malabsorptive conditions) and neural tube defects (family history or previous child with neural tube defect). \u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Folate deficiency during early pregnancy increases the risk of neural tube defects, particularly spina bifida.","Adequate folate supplementation before and during early pregnancy reduces the risk of neural tube defects by approximately 70%.","Neural tube closure occurs by day 28 of pregnancy, making early folate supplementation crucial."],"references":["Ledet Iii LF, Plaisance CJ, Daniel CP, Wagner MJ, Alvarez I, Burroughs CR, Rieger R, Siddaiah H, Ahmadzadeh S, Shekoohi S, Kaye AD, Varrassi G. Spina Bifida Prevention: A Narrative Review of Folic Acid Supplements for Childbearing Age Women. Cureus. 2024 Jan 26;16(1):e53008. doi: 10.7759/cureus.53008. PMID: 38406082; PMCID: PMC10894015.","Safi J, Joyeux L, Chalouhi GE. Periconceptional folate deficiency and implications in neural tube defects. J Pregnancy. 2012;2012:295083. doi: 10.1155/2012/295083. Epub 2012 Aug 5. PMID: 22900183; PMCID: PMC3415073.","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press.","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51456"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16149"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51456","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51456"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-28T17:38:56+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-28T17:39:12+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8840"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66006"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"23","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/23"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd30","name":"Obstetrics","synonyms":null,"descrip